## Why this rule exists

2026-07-14: a daily-DD kill-switch self-recovery fix — a production
reliability change for the demo-MT5 agent that the user had declared runs
on `main` this session — was delegated without a target-branch pin. The
worker committed and pushed to the checked-out branch, `next-gen`, which
is the unrelated v2 platform line. Cherry-pick to `main` recovered the
change; the wrong-branch commit (`d6e0e4a` on `next-gen`) was left alone.
Root cause: the delegating agent did not carry the user's per-session
branch declaration into the delegation prompt.
